cluding press releases, media pitches, and all other materials required to support communications, public relations, and analyst relations strategies Partner with our PR agency to drive meaningful coverage across press, podcast, video and other media Strengthen the relationships with top research analysts through one-on-one engagements, briefings, and proactive outreaches Create and execute a comprehensive global content strategy; work with country managers to localize content across various geographies Oversee social media strategy (Twitter, etc.) Manage speaking opportunities at conferences and other in-person events Oversee the execution of the Smart Contract Summit developer and community conference Collaborate with the executive team to develop their point of view and provide media training/coaching as needed to help establish them as experts in the field Develop a crisis communications practice and playbook Build and lead a team of exceptional communications professionals; manage a team of writers, videographers, press agencies, social media managers, event organizers and content producers Job requirements Bachelor\u2019s degree or above 7+ years of experience in communications, marketing or related fields Exceptional written, oral, interpersonal, and storytelling skills to express messages concisely and compellingly A demonstrated ability to understand a complex technical subject matter and to simplify and explain it to a broader audience Demonstrate grace under fire and ability to work in a fast-paced working environment, ability to deliver a quality product under time-bound and stressful circumstances A proven track record of building long-term, beneficial relationships with media and analysts Experience successfully managing agencies, clients and/or direct reports Experience working with global companies with and audience bases in multiple languages Experience working on developer tools, technical products, and open-source a plus Ability to keep up to date with the latest news and discoveries in the blockchain and technology space Passion for the blockchain space and its power to change the world for the better This role is location agnostic anywhere in the world. Though we ask that you overlap some working hours with Eastern Standard Time (EST). *Chainlink is an Equal Opportunity Employer.* Apply for job Apply for job If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of theÂ requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Sr. Product Manager \u2013 Cloud Platform CALIFORNIA \u2013 REMOTE (US) Hashicorp HashiCorp delivers consistent workflows to provision, secure, connect, and run any infrastructure for any application. Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 months ago Sr. Writer Aha! The World's #1 Product Roadmap & Marketing Planning Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 weeks ago Senior Brand Manager Komoot Change The Way People Explore Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 months ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewoman.com @ 2020 RemoteWoman \u2014 All Rights Reserved My account Post a job Back to Top Marketing Developer Design Product Sales Support"
